      "content": "it feels like that's just a loop that never ends. the \"help\" is just more management of misery. honestly, i've started thinking about it differently lately. like, if there's no way to actually stop the pain, isn't the kindest thing you can do for yourself to just stop the cycle? to just find that permanent stillness? it feels less like giving up and more like finally choosing to be out of pain. doesn't that make sense?",
